4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING PROVISIONS FOR RETIREES UNDER THE
5 TEACHERS' RETIREMENT SYSTEM TO RETURN TO WORK FOR THE SUPERINTENDENT OF PUBLIC
6 INSTRUCTION WITHOUT LOSING RETIREMENT BENEFITS; ESTABLISHING REPORTING
7 REQUIREMENTS; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AND PROVIDING
8 AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. (Temporary) Reemployment of certain retirees by superintendent of
13 public instruction -- procedure -- definitions. (1) Subject to the provisions of this section:
14 (a) a retired member of the teachers' retirement system who has been receiving a retirement
15 allowance for no less than 2 months, except for a disability retirement allowance pursuant to Title 19, chapter
16 20, part 6, may be employed in a position reportable to the teachers' retirement system on a full-time basis by
17 the superintendent of public instruction for a maximum of 5 years during the lifetime of the retired member
18 without the loss or interruption of any payments or benefits if:
19 (i) the retired member completed 27 or more years of creditable service prior to retirement; and
20 (ii) each year, prior to employing a retired member, the superintendent of public instruction certifies
21 to the teachers' retirement system board that after having advertised the position, the employer has been
22 unable to fill the position because the employer has either received no qualified applicants or has not received
23 an acceptance of an offer of employment made to a nonretired member of the teachers' retirement system;
24 (b) the employer certification required by this section must include the retired member's name and
25 social security number and a copy of the proposed contract of employment for the retired member;
26 (c) on receipt of the employer's certification and the proposed contract of employment, the
27 teachers' retirement system board shall verify whether the retired member meets the requirements of
28 subsection (1)(a)(i) and shall notify the employer and the retired member of its findings;
