1 (d) a retired member reemployed under this section is ineligible for active membership under 19-
2 20-302 and is ineligible to receive service credit under any retirement system identified in Title 19; and
3 (e) the board shall report biennially to the education interim committee and the state administration
4 and veterans' affairs interim committee in accordance with 5-11-210 regarding the implementation of and
5 results arising from this section.
6 (2) An employer employing a retired member pursuant to this section shall contribute monthly to
7 the teachers' retirement system an amount equal to the sum of the contribution rates provided in 19-20-602, 19-
8 20-604, 19-20-605, 19-20-608, and 19-20-609.
9 (3) A retired member reemployed pursuant to this section is exempt from the earnings and
10 employment limits provided in 19-20-731.
11 (4) The board may adopt rules to implement this section.
12 (5) As used in this section, the following definitions apply:
13 (a) "Employer" means the superintendent of public instruction as described in 20-3-101 that
14 employs a retired member of the teachers' retirement system.
15 (b) "System" means the teachers' retirement system.
16 (c) "Year" means all or any part of a fiscal year running July 1 through June 30.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
19 integral part of Title 19, chapter 20, part 7, and the provisions of Title 19, chapter 20, part 7, apply to [section 1].
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2031.
